            . I live in <placeName id="t18310630-290-crimeloc1524">Taylor's-row, St. John-street-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-290-crimeloc1524" type="placeName" value="Taylor's-row, St. John-street-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-290-crimeloc1524" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-290-off1522 t18310630-290-crimeloc1524"></join>. The prisoner came to my lodging on the 6th of June, between nine and ten o'clock in the morning- I had known him some time; he stopped till about a quarter-past one, and at half-past I missed a musical snuffbox, which I had to repair for Susannah Morgan; it was in my second-floor back-room, which is a workshop - he was in that room most of the time; it was at the end of the work-bench - I saw it safe about twelve o'clock, and nobody called after that; I had him taken at his lodging in Windmill-street, Haymarket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did not you suspect another person? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-290-person2083">
                  PETER 
                  DIXON
               <interp inst="t18310630-290-person2083" type="surname" value="DIXON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-290-person2083" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-290-person2083" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Howes, a pawnbroker. This musical-box was pawned on the 6th of June, between one and two o'clock, by the prisoner, for 2l.; I am quite certain of his person - it was claimed next morning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-290-person2084">
